The paper proposes a new method for training Support Vector Data Description (SVDD) which is a popular technique in machine learning for outlier detection. The paper focuses on the computational efficiency of the method for large datasets, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the method involves iterative sampling, which is a common technique in Data Mining (cs.DM) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) applications. Finally, the use of Support Vector Machines (SVMs) in the SVDD method suggests that it may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
